    "attributes": {
        "action": "Adopt the STV voting system for a more representative government.",
        "additional_details": "Let\u2019s imagine a new country adopts the system and holds the first election. The results are-\r\nBlue- 27% of votes \r\nGreen-32% of votes\r\nRed-21% of votes\r\nYellow-20% of votes.\r\nGreen party wins with only 32% of the country\u2019s representatives but is elected PM (68% of the country is unrepresented).\r\nThis is the system we have in the UK. \r\nI don\u2019t have enough characters left to explain the benefits of STV, but please use these videos to learn-\r\nhttps://youtu.be/P38Y4VG1Ibo\r\nhttps://youtu.be/l8XOZJkozfI",
        "background": "Our current FPTP voting system is extremely flawed. The system has been in use for so long that, just like the USA, we are stuck in a two-party system that we will never be able to break out of.",
